Title: DOOR / HATCH: REAR DOOR: DISASSEMBLY; 2021 - 2022 MY Prius [07/2020 -        ]

DISASSEMBLY

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

The necessary procedures (adjustment, calibration, initialization, or registration) that must be performed after parts are removed and installed, or replaced during rear door removal/installation are shown below.

Necessary Procedure After Parts Removed/Installed/Replaced

Replaced Part or Performed Procedure

Necessary Procedure

Effect/Inoperative Function when Necessary Procedure not Performed

Link

Disconnect cable from negative auxiliary battery terminal

Memorize steering angle neutral point

Lane Tracing Assist System

Intelligent clearance sonar system*1

Simple advanced parking guidance system*1

Pre-collision system

AFS (Adaptive Front-lighting System)

Initialize back door lock

Power door lock control system

  • Door window regulator sub-assembly
  • Door glass
  • Door glass run

Initialize Power Window Control System

  • Auto up and down function
  • Jam protection function
  • Catch protection function
  • Remote control function
  • Key-linked function
  • Wireless transmitter-linked function
  • Key-off operation function
  • Window open warning function

*1: When performing learning using the Techstream: Click here

HINT:

  • Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.
  • The following procedure is for the LH side.

PROCEDURE

1. PRECAUTION

NOTICE:

After turning the power switch off, waiting time may be required before disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal. Therefore, make sure to read the disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal notices before proceeding with work.

Click here

2. DISCONNECT CABLE FROM NEGATIVE AUXILIARY BATTERY TERMINAL

NOTICE:

When disconnecting the cable, some systems need to be initialized after the cable is reconnected.

Click here

3. REMOVE REAR DOOR INSIDE HANDLE BEZEL PLUG

(a) Using a moulding remover, disengage the 3 claws to remove the rear door inside handle bezel plug.

4. REMOVE REAR ARMREST ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 3 clips and 7 claws to remove the rear armrest assembly as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

5. REMOVE REAR POWER WINDOW REGULATOR SWITCH ASSEMBLY WITH REAR DOOR UPPER ARMREST BASE PANEL

(a) Disengage the 2 clips and 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

(b) Disconnect the connector to remove the rear power window regulator switch assembly with rear door upper armrest base panel.

6. REMOVE REAR DOOR TRIM BOARD SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Apply protective tape to the rear door panel as shown in the illustration.

Protective Tape

(b) Remove the 3 screws.

(c) Using a clip remover, disengage the 8 clips.

(d) Pull out the rear door trim board sub-assembly as shown in the illustration to disengage the guide.

Remove in this Direction

(e) Raise the rear door trim board sub-assembly to separate the rear door trim board sub-assembly with the rear door inner glass weatherstrip and No. 1 door scuff plate clamp.

(f) Disconnect the rear door lock remote control cable assembly and rear door inside locking cable assembly to remove the rear door trim board sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

*1

Rear Door Inside Locking Cable Assembly

*2

Rear Door Lock Remote Control Cable Assembly

Remove in this Direction

(g) Using a screwdriver, disengage the claw to remove the No. 1 door scuff plate clamp from the rear door trim board sub-assembly.

7. REMOVE REAR DOOR INNER GLASS WEATHERSTRIP WITH REAR DOOR NO. 2 VENT SEAL

(a) Disengage the 5 claws to remove the rear door inner glass weatherstrip with rear door No. 2 vent seal.

8. REMOVE REAR DOOR NO. 2 VENT SEAL

(a) Remove the rear door No. 2 vent seal from the rear door inner glass weatherstrip.

Remove in this Direction

9. REMOVE REAR DOOR INSIDE HANDLE SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the rear door inside handle sub-assembly.

10. REMOVE REAR SPEAKER ASSEMBLY

Click here

11. REMOVE REAR DOOR FRAME GARNISH

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the rear door frame garnish.

12. REMOVE REAR DOOR SERVICE HOLE COVER

(a) Remove the rear door service hole cover.

HINT:

Remove any remaining butyl tape from the rear door panel.

13. REMOVE REAR DOOR PANEL PROTECTOR

(a) Remove the rear door panel protector.

14. REMOVE REAR DOOR NO. 2 SERVICE HOLE COVER

(a) Remove the rear door No. 2 service hole cover.

15. REMOVE REAR DOOR GLASS RUN

(a) Remove the rear door glass run.

16. REMOVE REAR DOOR CHECK ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the 3 bolts and rear door check assembly.

17. REMOVE REAR DOOR WEATHERSTRIP

(a) Using a clip remover, disengage the 25 clips and remove the rear door weatherstrip.

*a

Double-sided Tape

18. REMOVE REAR DOOR WINDOW DIVISION BAR SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the screw, 2 bolts and rear door window division bar sub-assembly.

Screw

Bolt

19. REMOVE REAR DOOR QUARTER WINDOW GLASS

(a) Remove the rear door quarter window glass with rear door quarter window weatherstrip as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

(b) Remove the rear door quarter window glass from the rear door quarter window weatherstrip.

20. REMOVE REAR DOOR GLASS SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Separate the rear door glass sub-assembly from the rear door window regulator assembly as shown in the illustration.

NOTICE:

After separating the rear door glass sub-assembly, do not allow it to fall.

(b) Remove the rear door glass sub-assembly.

NOTICE:

Do not damage the rear door glass sub-assembly.

Remove in this Direction (1)

Remove in this Direction (2)

21. REMOVE REAR DOOR GLASS CHANNEL SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Using a screwdriver, remove the rear door glass channel sub-assembly.

HINT:

Tape the screwdriver tip before use.

*a

Protective Tape

22. REMOVE REAR DOOR GLASS CHANNEL FILLER

(a) Remove the rear door glass channel filler from the rear door glass sub-assembly.

23. REMOVE REAR DOOR WINDOW REGULATOR ASSEMBLY

(a) Disconnect the connector.

(b) Loosen the temporary bolt.

NOTICE:

Do not remove the temporary bolt. If the temporary bolt is removed, the rear door window regulator assembly may fall and cause damage.

*a

Temporary Bolt

(c) Remove the 3 bolts and rear door window regulator assembly.

(d) Remove the temporary bolt from the rear door window regulator assembly.

24. REMOVE REAR DOOR LOCK WITH MOTOR ASSEMBLY

Click here

25. REMOVE REAR DOOR OUTSIDE HANDLE ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 2 claws and move the lever as shown in the illustration.

(b) Remove the rear door outside handle assembly as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

26. REMOVE REAR DOOR OUTSIDE HANDLE COVER

(a) Using a T30 "TORX" socket wrench, loosen the screw.

HINT:

The screw cannot be removed because it is integrated into the rear door outside handle frame sub-assembly.

(b) Disengage the claw to remove the rear door outside handle cover.

27. REMOVE REAR DOOR FRONT OUTSIDE HANDLE PAD

(a) Disengage the 3 claws to remove the rear door front outside handle pad.

28. REMOVE REAR DOOR REAR OUTSIDE HANDLE PAD

(a) Disengage the claw and 3 guides to remove the rear door rear outside handle pad.

29. REMOVE REAR DOOR OUTSIDE HANDLE FRAME SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Using a T30 "TORX" socket wrench, remove the screw.

*A

Inside

*B

Outside

(b) Slide the rear door outside handle frame sub-assembly to disengage the claw, and then remove it.

30. REMOVE REAR DOOR PANEL CUSHION

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the rear door panel cushion.

31. REMOVE REAR DOOR DUST PROOF SEAL

(a) Disengage the 3 claws to remove the 3 rear door dust proof seals.

32. REMOVE REAR DOOR NO. 3 WEATHERSTRIP

(a) Disengage the claw and remove the rear door No. 3 weatherstrip.

Double-sided Tape

Click here

35. REMOVE REAR DOOR UPPER WINDOW FRAME MOULDING

Click here

36. REMOVE REAR DOOR REAR WINDOW FRAME MOULDING

Click here

Click here

38. REMOVE REAR DOOR OUTSIDE STRIPE (w/ Black Out Tape)

Click here

39. REMOVE REAR DOOR UPPER OUTSIDE STRIPE (w/ Black Out Tape)
